723465f-b.title: Manhattan: Sullivan Street - Prince Street
723465f-b.text:
Sullivan Street (through the center), north from Prinoe Street
(across the foreground), showing in View No. 1 the west side of the
street and in No. 2 the east side. The two Prince Street structures
shown at the left are No's 191 and 193, at and adjoining the N.W.
corner of Sullivan Street.
May 7, 1928.
P. L. Sperr .
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

722667f-a.title: Manhattan: Prince Street - Sullivan Street
722667f-a.text:
Prince Street, east from Sullivan Street, showing demolition work in
progress on three houses, Nos. 175 to 171, west of, adjoining and at the
N.W. corner of Thompson Street. Also shown is a portion of the Sixth Ave.
Elevated Line on West Broadway.
May 20, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
